KW  - Volatility of implied volatility
KW  - Uncertainty about uncertainty
KW  - Uncertainty about risk
AB  - In this paper, we examine how uncertainty about risk, based on firm estimates of volatility of implied volatility (VIV) affects mergers and acquisitions. We show that uncertainty about risk, captured by firm estimates of volatility of implied volatility (VIV) affects both bidder and target announcement returns and the method of payment. For high-risk firms, bidder firm VIV negatively effects the likelihood of a cash-only offer. For low-risk firms, bidder firms (target firms) VIV negatively (positively) affects bidder firm's announcement returns. Target announcement returns for low-risk firms are negatively related to bidder firm VIV. When we control for the volatility level using firm estimates of average implied volatility, VIV effects on announcement returns are sustained. However, average volatility effects subsume bidder firm VIV effects on the method of payment. Furthermore, high risk bidder firms revise their offer price upward with an increase in bidder VIV for non-cash offers.
ER  - 

